Intellectual Property (IP) management is a critical aspect of business strategy, ensuring that companies project their innovations, inventions, and creative works. To effectively navigate the complex landscape of intellectual property, organizations employ various tools and frameworks. This article delves into IP management frameworks, patent filling tools, and IP portfolio analytics, providing a comprehensive understanding of each. As technology and business landscapes evolve, so does the field of IP management. The digitization of processes has led to the development of innovative tools and methodologies for managing intellectual property. Cloud-based solutions, artificial intelligence, and machine learning are increasingly integrated into IP management frameworks, enabling more efficient identification, protection, and management of intellectual assets.
